{# templates/roadmaps/real-state/house-hacking.html.twig #}
{% extends 'base-roadmaps.html.twig' %}

{% block stylesheets %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_link_tags('real_state_css') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block javascripts %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_script_tags('real_state_js') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    <div class="container">
        <!-- Article Hero -->
        <div class="article-hero animate" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2f2a24 0%, #5e4b3f 100%);">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <div class="hero-icon" style="background-color: var(--real-estate-color);">
                    <i class="fas fa-people-roof"></i>
                </div>
                <h1>House Hacking <span>Live for Free and Build Wealth</span></h1>
                <p class="hero-description">
                    Buy a multi‑unit property, live in one unit, and rent the others. Learn how house hacking can drastically reduce your living expenses and jumpstart your real estate investing journey.
                </p>
                <div class="phase-tag" style="background-color: rgba(225,112,85,0.2); color: #f7b9a9;">
                    <i class="fas fa-layer-group"></i> Phase 4: Skill Building · 8 min read
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Introduction -->
        <section class="animate">
            <h2 class="section-title">🏘️ What is House Hacking?</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                House hacking is the strategy of buying a small multi‑family property (duplex, triplex, fourplex), living in one unit, and renting out the others.
                The rental income can cover most or all of your mortgage, letting you live for free while building equity and landlord experience.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Key Benefits Grid -->
        <div class="rule-grid animate">
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-home"></i> Live for Free (or Cheap)</h4>
                <p>Rental income from other units can offset your housing costs, sometimes turning a negative expense into positive cash flow.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> Build Equity</h4>
                <p>Your tenants pay down your mortgage, building wealth while you sleep. Over time, appreciation adds to your net worth.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-graduation-cap"></i> Learn Landlording</h4>
                <p>Start small with tenants next door. You'll learn maintenance, tenant management, and the ropes without a huge portfolio.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-hand-holding-usd"></i> Low Down Payment</h4>
                <p>FHA loans allow as little as 3.5% down on 2‑4 unit properties if you live in one. Conventional loans also have low down payment options for owner‑occupants.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Deeper Dive Card -->
        <div class="card animate">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> How to Get Started</h3>
            <p><strong>1. Find a property</strong> – Look for duplexes, triplexes, or fourplexes in your area. Use an FHA loan if you're a first‑timer.</p>
            <p><strong>2. Run the numbers</strong> – Estimate rental income from other units, factor in expenses, and ensure you can cover the mortgage even if vacant.</p>
            <p><strong>3. Live there</strong> – You must occupy the property for at least one year to satisfy owner‑occupancy requirements.</p>
            <p><strong>4. Rinse and repeat</strong> – After a year, you can move out, rent your unit, and repeat the process with another property.</p>
            <p style="background: var(--light-gray); padding: 15px; border-radius: 12px;">
                <strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Some investors start with a single‑family home and rent out rooms. That's also house hacking! The principle is the same: use rental income to reduce your living costs.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Interactive Tool: House Hacking Savings Calculator (disabled for non-logged-in) -->
        <div class="card animate" id="house-hacking-calculator">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-calculator"></i> Interactive: House Hacking Savings Calculator</h3>
            <p>See how much you can save (or earn) by renting out part of your property.</p>

            <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0;">
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Purchase Price ($) <span id="priceValHH">300000</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="priceHH" min="50000" max="1000000" value="300000" step="5000" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Down Payment (%) <span id="downPercentValHH">10</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="downPercentHH" min="3" max="50" value="10" step="1" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Interest Rate (%) <span id="rateValHH">6.5</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="rateHH" min="2" max="10" value="6.5" step="0.125" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Loan Term (years) </label>
                    <select id="termHH" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                        <option value="15">15 years</option>
                        <option value="30" selected>30 years</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Monthly Rent from Other Units ($) <span id="rentValHH">1500</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="rentHH" min="0" max="5000" value="1500" step="50" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Your Current Rent/Living Cost ($) <span id="currentRentValHH">1200</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="currentRentHH" min="0" max="5000" value="1200" step="50" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Other Monthly Expenses (tax/ins/maintenance) <span id="expensesValHH">500</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="expensesHH" min="0" max="2000" value="500" step="50" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
                <button id="calcHouseHack" class="btn-outline">Calculate Savings</button>
            </div>

            <div id="houseHackResult" style="margin-top: 25px; padding: 20px; background: var(--light-color); border-radius: 12px;">
                <p>Adjust the values and click the button.</p>
            </div>

            <p class="pro-tip" style="margin-top: 15px;">
                <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> This calculator estimates your mortgage payment and compares your net housing cost after rental income to your current rent. It does not include vacancy, repairs, or property management – always budget for those.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Quiz Section -->
        {% if app.user and quiz is defined and quiz %}
            {# Logged in user – quiz already taken #}
            <div class="quiz-container animate" style="background: #2f2a24;">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">🧠 You've already taken this quiz</h3>
                <p style="color: #e2e8f0; font-size: 1.2rem;">
                    Your score: <strong>{{ quiz.quizzScore }}%</strong>
                </p>
                <p style="color: #cbd5e0;">
                    You can retake the quiz to improve your score. Click the button below to reset it.
                </p>
                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'house-hacking', retake: 1 }) }}"
                       class="btn"
                       style="background-color: #e17055; color: white; text-decoration: none;">
                        Retake Quiz
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        {% else %}
            {# Show quiz (interactivity blocked by JS if not logged in) #}
            <div class="quiz-container animate" data-page-id="{{ page.id }}" style="background: #2f2a24;">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">📝 Test Your Knowledge: House Hacking</h3>

                <div class="quiz-question">1. What is house hacking?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="1">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Breaking into a house illegally</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Living in one unit of a multi‑unit property while renting the others</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Flipping houses quickly</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Using Airbnb to rent your primary residence</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">2. Which loan type is commonly used by first‑time house hackers?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="2">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">FHA (3.5% down)</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">VA (requires military)</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">USDA (rural only)</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Jumbo</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">3. To qualify for owner‑occupant financing, you typically must live in the property for at least:</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="3">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">6 months</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">1 year</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">2 years</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">No requirement</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">4. Which of the following is a benefit of house hacking?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="4">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">No maintenance responsibilities</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Rental income reduces your housing costs</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">You never have to deal with tenants</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Property taxes are eliminated</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">5. After one year of house hacking, you can:</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="5">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Sell the property tax‑free</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Move out, rent your unit, and repeat the process</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Refinance with no costs</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Stop paying mortgage</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <button id="quiz-submit" class="btn" style="background-color: var(--real-estate-color);">Get score & submit</button>
                </div>
                <div class="quiz-result"></div>
            </div>
        {% endif %}

        <!-- Next Steps in Phase 4 -->
        <section style="margin: 60px 0;">
            <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: center;">📘 Continue Phase 4: Skill Building</h2>
            <div class="next-steps">
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'brrrr-method' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-arrows-rotate"></i>
                    <h3>BRRRR Method</h3>
                    <p>Buy, Rehab, Rent, Refinance, Repeat.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'syndications-crowdfunding' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-users"></i>
                    <h3>Real Estate Syndications</h3>
                    <p>Pool money to buy larger properties.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'scaling-real-estate-portfolio' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-chart-gantt"></i>
                    <h3>Scaling Your Portfolio</h3>
                    <p>Grow without burning out.</p>
                </a>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
